From: Zhong Hongbo <hongbo.zhong@windriver.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Feb 2014 14:20:28 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1069/1072] sound: hdmi : Fix the error HDMI option

Correct it to mach the general hdmi codec. reference the commit:

commit 2d01fe75a9dd29319eb233b46f2adcf17d89002e
Author: Barry Song <21cnbao@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu May 16 14:08:07 2013 +0800

    ASoC: omap-hdmi-codec: make the driver common for other SoCs

    to support HDMI on CSR SiRFprimaII and atlasVI, we need one more HDMI pseudo
    codec, rather than add a new driver, we can make omap HDMI codec common for
    other SoCs as well. then the omap-hdmi codec becomes a generic HDMI pseudo-
    codec as HDMI audio features depend on HDMI specification not on SoCs.

    Signed-off-by: Barry Song <Baohua.Song@csr.com>
    Signed-off-by: Mark Brown <broonie@linaro.org>
    (cherry picked from commit bf7c6e6ccbde22c96c5c1e5cec08740c31229df1)
    Signed-off-by: Zumeng Chen <zumeng.chen@windriver.com>

Signed-off-by: Zhong Hongbo <hongbo.zhong@windriver.com>
---
 sound/soc/fsl/Kconfig |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/fsl/Kconfig b/sound/soc/fsl/Kconfig
index 8e8f144..3ba3ae4 100644
--- a/sound/soc/fsl/Kconfig
+++ b/sound/soc/fsl/Kconfig
@@ -245,7 +245,7 @@ config SND_SOC_IMX_HDMI
 	depends on MFD_MXC_HDMI
 	select SND_SOC_IMX_HDMI_DMA
 	select SND_SOC_FSL_HDMI
-	select SND_SOC_OMAP_HDMI_CODEC
+	select SND_SOC_HDMI_CODEC
 	help
 	  SoC Audio support for i.MX boards with HDMI audio
 	  Say Y if you want to add support for SoC audio on an i.MX board with
